  "root_text": {
    "sn2.20:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 2.20 ",
    "sn2.20:0.2": "2. Anāthapiṇḍikavagga ",
    "sn2.20:0.3": "Anāthapiṇḍikasutta ",
    "sn2.20:1.1": "Ekamantaṁ ṭhito kho anāthapiṇḍiko devaputto bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
    "sn2.20:2.1": "“Idañhi taṁ jetavanaṁ, ",
    "sn2.20:2.2": "isisaṅghanisevitaṁ; ",
    "sn2.20:2.3": "Āvutthaṁ dhammarājena, ",
    "sn2.20:2.4": "pītisañjananaṁ mama. ",
    "sn2.20:3.1": "Kammaṁ vijjā ca dhammo ca, ",
    "sn2.20:3.2": "sīlaṁ jīvitamuttamaṁ; ",
    "sn2.20:3.3": "Etena maccā sujjhanti, ",
    "sn2.20:3.4": "na gottena dhanena vā. ",
    "sn2.20:4.1": "Tasmā hi paṇḍito poso, ",
    "sn2.20:4.2": "sampassaṁ atthamattano; ",
    "sn2.20:4.3": "Yoniso vicine dhammaṁ, ",
    "sn2.20:4.4": "evaṁ tattha visujjhati. ",
    "sn2.20:5.1": "Sāriputtova paññāya, ",
    "sn2.20:5.2": "sīlena upasamena ca; ",
    "sn2.20:5.3": "Yopi pāraṅgato bhikkhu, ",
    "sn2.20:5.4": "etāvaparamo siyā”ti. ",
    "sn2.20:6.1": "Idamavoca anāthapiṇḍiko devaputto. ",
    "sn2.20:6.2": "Idaṁ vatvā bhagavantaṁ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṁ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi. ",
    "sn2.20:7.1": "Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
    "sn2.20:7.2": "“imaṁ, bhikkhave, rattiṁ aññataro devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṁ jetavanaṁ obhāsetvā yenāhaṁ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṁ abhivādetvā ekamantaṁ aṭṭhāsi. ",
    "sn2.20:7.3": "Ekamantaṁ ṭhito kho, bhikkhave, so devaputto mama santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
    "sn2.20:8.1": "‘Idañhi taṁ jetavanaṁ, ",
    "sn2.20:8.2": "isisaṅghanisevitaṁ; ",
    "sn2.20:8.3": "Āvutthaṁ dhammarājena, ",
    "sn2.20:8.4": "pītisañjananaṁ mama. ",
    "sn2.20:9.1": "Kammaṁ vijjā ca dhammo ca, ",
    "sn2.20:9.2": "sīlaṁ jīvitamuttamaṁ; ",
    "sn2.20:9.3": "Etena maccā sujjhanti, ",
    "sn2.20:9.4": "na gottena dhanena vā. ",
    "sn2.20:10.1": "Tasmā hi paṇḍito poso, ",
    "sn2.20:10.2": "sampassaṁ atthamattano; ",
    "sn2.20:10.3": "Yoniso vicine dhammaṁ, ",
    "sn2.20:10.4": "evaṁ tattha visujjhati. ",
    "sn2.20:11.1": "Sāriputtova paññāya, ",
    "sn2.20:11.2": "sīlena upasamena ca; ",
    "sn2.20:11.3": "Yopi pāraṅgato bhikkhu, ",
    "sn2.20:11.4": "etāvaparamo siyā’ti. ",
    "sn2.20:12.1": "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, so devaputto. ",
    "sn2.20:12.2": "Idaṁ vatvā maṁ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṁ katvā tatthevantaradhāyī”ti. ",
    "sn2.20:13.1": "Evaṁ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "sn2.20:13.2": "“so hi nūna, bhante, anāthapiṇḍiko devaputto bhavissati. ",
    "sn2.20:13.3": "Anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati āyasmante sāriputte abhippasanno ahosī”ti. ",
    "sn2.20:13.4": "“Sādhu sādhu, ānanda, yāvatakaṁ kho, ānanda, takkāya pattabbaṁ anuppattaṁ taṁ tayā. ",
    "sn2.20:13.5": "Anāthapiṇḍiko hi so, ānanda, devaputto”ti. ",
    "sn2.20:13.6": "Anāthapiṇḍikavaggo dutiyo. ",
    "sn2.20:14.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "sn2.20:14.1": "Candimaso ca veṇḍu ca, ",
    "sn2.20:14.2": "Dīghalaṭṭhi ca nandano; ",
    "sn2.20:14.3": "Candano vāsudatto ca, ",
    "sn2.20:14.4": "Subrahmā kakudhena ca; ",
    "sn2.20:14.5": "Uttaro navamo vutto, ",
    "sn2.20:14.6": "Dasamo anāthapiṇḍikoti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn2.20:0.1": "Linked Discourses 2.20 ",
    "sn2.20:0.2": "2. With Anāthapiṇḍika ",
    "sn2.20:0.3": "With Anāthapiṇḍika ",
    "sn2.20:1.1": "Standing to one side, the godling Anāthapiṇḍika recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: ",
    "sn2.20:2.1": "“This is indeed that Jeta’s Grove, ",
    "sn2.20:2.2": "frequented by the Saṅgha of seers, ",
    "sn2.20:2.3": "where the King of Dhamma stayed: ",
    "sn2.20:2.4": "it brings me joy! ",
    "sn2.20:3.1": "Deeds, knowledge, and principle; ",
    "sn2.20:3.2": "ethical conduct, an excellent livelihood; ",
    "sn2.20:3.3": "by these are mortals purified, ",
    "sn2.20:3.4": "not by clan or wealth. ",
    "sn2.20:4.1": "That’s why an astute person, ",
    "sn2.20:4.2": "seeing what’s good for themselves, ",
    "sn2.20:4.3": "would examine the teaching rationally, ",
    "sn2.20:4.4": "and thus be purified in it. ",
    "sn2.20:5.1": "Sāriputta is full of wisdom, ",
    "sn2.20:5.2": "ethics, and peace. ",
    "sn2.20:5.3": "Even a mendicant who has crossed over ",
    "sn2.20:5.4": "might at best equal him.” ",
    "sn2.20:6.1": "This is what the godling Anāthapiṇḍika said. ",
    "sn2.20:6.2": "Then he bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right side, before vanishing right there. ",
    "sn2.20:7.1": "Then, when the night had passed, the Buddha addressed the mendicants: ",
    "sn2.20:7.2": "“Mendicants, tonight, a certain glorious godling, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, came to me, bowed, stood to one side, ",
    "sn2.20:7.3": "and recited these verses in my presence.” The Buddha then repeated the verses in full. ",
